  "text": "Below we will study how the patenting behavior of German university professors changed after the 2002 reform. Studying these changes is warranted, first, by the ongoing controversy over the merits of the US Bayh -Dole Act. Second, it cannot be presumed that the German reform brought about the same effects as the Bayh -Dole Act (or similar reforms in other countries; cf. [CITATION_1] Della Malva et al., forthcoming; [CITATION_2] Professors' privilege IPR owned by the public agency which funds a university University owns and exploits patents D USA",
